He  has been tracking the progress of Wales, who under manager Chris Coleman, have qualified for a major tournament finals for the first time since the 1958 World Cup.
''I wish Wales very well. Of course I want Ukraine to do well. But I have been following Wales a little bit," he said.
"The team is improving a lot. I wish them the best.''
Ukraine will be in Euro 2016 Group C with Germany, Poland and Northern Ireland. They kick off against Germany, in Lille, on 12 June.
