Andriy Yarmolenko, who is the second highest Ukraine goalscorer, scored his 23rd international goal to give his side victory over Wales, who face Slovakia, England and Russia in France.
Shevchenko was happy with the Ukraine victory at the stadium which staged the 2012 final, but is aware Wales will be a different proposition at the Euro 2016 finals when Bale and Arsenal's Aaron Ramsey are in action.
''The coach [Chris Coleman] missed them, but it was good for us,'' said former Chelsea player Shevchenko.
